To connect remotely to a server, we use SSH connection (secure shell connection) 

The diffult port for SSH is Port 22

To connect remotely we need the following:

1. IP address of the machine/server we want to connect to.
2. A User
3. Keypair
4. Third party tool from which we will connect on (e.g Mobaxterm)


Yum is a package manager in linux 
A package manager is used to install packages

yum in centos linux
apt-get for ubuntu linux


 list hidden files and directories we use the command # ls -a
 To make a directory                                  # mkdir + directory  name
